HEADWORD: Butchers broom
<hw>Butch"er's broom`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of plants (<gen>Ruscus</gen>); esp. <spn>Ruscus aculeatus</spn>,
which has large red berries and leaflike branches. See
<er>Cladophyll</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

